1. Pobednik (nominative) ovogodišnjeg takmičenja je mladi teniser iz Novog Sada. (*Winner*) (The winner of this year's competition is a young tennis player from Novi Sad.)
2. Voleo bih da postanem pobednik (nominative) ovog maratona. (*Victor*) (I would like to become the victor of this marathon.)
3. Naša ekipa je slavila pobedu, ali pravi pobednik (nominative) je bio fer plej. (*Champion*) (Our team celebrated the victory, but fair play was the real champion.)
4. Danas smo svedoci pobedničkog (genitive) duha naših sportista. (*Winning*) (Today we are witnessing the winning spirit of our athletes.)
5. Bio je tako ponosan na svoj pobednički (genitive) pehar da ga je pokazivao svakom ko je došao u posetu. (*Victorious*) (He was so proud of his victorious trophy that he showed it to everyone who came to visit.)
6. Čovek koji nikada nije doživeo poraz nije pravi pobednik (nominative). (*Winner*) (A man who has never experienced defeat is not a true winner.)
7. Timski rad je ključni faktor u ostvarivanju pobedničkih (genitive) rezultata. (*Winning*) (Teamwork is a key factor in achieving winning results.)
8. Pobedničko (adjective) postolje bilo je rezervisano za tri najbolja takmičara. (*Victorious*) (The victorious podium was reserved for the top three competitors.)
9. Na kraju dana, najvažnije je da se osećate kao pobednik (nominative). (*Victor*) (At the end of the day, the most important thing is to feel like a victor.)